This classification is supported by 59 out of 75 antivirus engines detecting it as malicious, with several engines specifically identifying signatures related to Emotet. The file's unusual and potentially harmful behaviors—such as potential system changes and network communication—align with those seen in malware, particularly those performing credential theft or system compromise.
